<br>
1)  Linking to Outwar or any such site where you get benefits for someone clicking your link. For most all such sites this is against the terms of service, and we will follow up with them to get you removed from their program. <br>
<br>
2)  Linking to, advertising, or quoting any website which auctions or sells items, characters, or services for Everquest.<br>
<br>
3)  Goatse, Tubgirl, and other such &quot;hideous&quot; pics.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>General Rules</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
1)  No discusion or linking of any everquest-related hacks, cheats or exploits.  Also, no attempts to sell or trade characters and/or items.  Basically, if you're discussing breaking the Everquest EULA, you're breaking our rules as well.<br>
<br>
2)  No porn or linking to porn. This includes cartoon porn, animated porn GIF's, etc. <br>
<br>
3)  Do not post misleading thread titles. Moderators may change a thread title if they feel it is appropriate. <br>
<br>
4)  No personal attacks or flames.  No posting of 'real life' information is allowed, such as phone numbers, addresses, etc.  Also, this includes attacks and flames based on real life characteristics, such as hate speech, racial slurs, etc.   <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Exception:  Personal attacks and flames are permitted in the Rants &amp; Flames forum, but all of the other rules in this section still apply</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
5)  Posters that have demonstrated over a period of time to have no desire to contribute positively to the community may be removed if the admin or moderators feel that removal would be in the greater interest of the community. Such individuals may be more commonly referred to in internet lingo at 'trolls' or 'baiters'. Due to the nature of these bans, they are subject to review, and may be made temporary or reversed at the discretion of the administrators.<br>
<br>
6) The administrator of the VCC witholds all rights to moderate the forums within the spirit of the rules above. All actionable offenses and violations will be given due consideration by 'common sense', and may be punished more or less harshly depending on the severity of the act and the interpretation of the act by the administrators.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Posting limits for new users</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
